*how'd I know you're white?  Snicker.*

*are you mad that you aren't lucifer?  Jealous.  You can't have his fame.  You can't have his power.  You'll never rule the kingdom, kid.*

*but you sure are serving him - all except that I haven't heard you brandishing God yet, the way lucifer would have you do.*

*You're taking your turn driving someone else's car.  How... uniform.  Your words are schizophrenic goulash but you think you're dropping glitter bombs.  Delusion is a scary place to be when eternity arrives to edify.*

*what happens when vanity vanishes*
*and pride meets a pit, pried wide open*
*maybe the money stands for how much you'll pay*
*for who you've been*
*when phantoms take possession*
*of the hole in your soul*

*look at me!*
*I'm a bango puppet*
*look at me!*
*I'm a bango puppet*
